96. 35. non sine eausa. These words express a concession or recog· 60 nition. The Stoic does not reject the view in question, though he does not undertake to establish it by reasoning, because that is impossible for him to do, The universality of the view alone gives it a claim to recognition. Although he only allows it to hold good at first of individuals, and those the wisest, yet its universal acceptance proves to him that there must have been an anticipation of it in the minds os men.
